John Wood may refer to:


Actors/TV
* Mrs. John Wood (1831–1915), British actor in America along with her less notable husband John Wood.
* John Wood (English actor) (1930–2011), known for Shakespearean roles and his association with Tom Stoppard
* John Wood (Australian actor) (born 1946), star of the long-running police drama Blue Heelers
* Jack Wood (1924–2007), TV writer and director
* John Wood, birth name of actor John Fortune
* John Wood (Australian actor, 1909-1965)

Architects and designers
* John Wood, the Elder (1704–1754), English architect best known for Queen Square and the Circus in Bath, England
* John Wood, the Younger (1728–1782), his son, also an architect and best known for the Royal Crescent in Bath, England
* John Turtle Wood (1821–1890), British architect, engineer and archaeologist
* John Wood (design theorist), English design theorist
* John Wood (painter), English history and portrait painter (1801–1870), see Thomas Stothard

Military
* John Augustus Wood (1818–1878), British soldier, Victoria Cross recipient
* John Taylor Wood (1830–1904), officer in the U.S. Navy who became a captain in the Confederate Navy during the American Civil War
* John Shirley Wood (1888–1966), United States Army general

Political
* John Wood (died 1458), English Member of Parliament for Worcester and Worcestershire
* John Wood (Ipswich MP), English Member of Parliament Ipswich in 1420
* John Wood (speaker) (died 1484), English MP and Speaker of the House of Commons
* John Wood (Scottish courtier) (died 1570), Secretary to Regent Moray
* John Atwood (Assistant Governor) (1576–1644), also known as John Wood, Assistant Governor of the Plymouth Colony
* John Wood (Isle of Man governor), Governor of the Isle of Man, 1761–1777
* John J. Wood (1784–1874), U.S. Representative from New York
* John Wood (died 1856) (1788–1856), British Member of Parliament for Preston
* John Wood (governor) (1798–1880), U.S. politician, governor of Illinois, 1860–1861
* John M. Wood (1813–1864), U.S. Representative from Maine
* John Wood (congressman) (1816–1898), U.S. Representative from Pennsylvania, 1859–1861
* John Wood (Australian politician) (1829–1914), member of the Victorian and Tasmanian Legislative Assemblies
* John Fisher Wood (1852–1899), Canadian Member of Parliament, from Ontario
* John William Wood, Sr. (1855–1928), U.S. politician, North Carolina State Representative, founder of Benson, North Carolina
* Sir John Wood, 1st Baronet (1857–1951), British Member of Parliament
* John Travers Wood (1878–1954), U.S. Representative from Idaho, 1951–1953
* John Stephens Wood (1885–1968), chairman of the House Un-American Activities Committee
* John Graeme Wood (1933–2007), veteran of British far-right politics and member of the British Peoples Party
* John F. Wood, Jr. (born 1936), U.S. politician, Maryland House of Delegates
* John Wood (diplomat) (born 1944), New Zealand diplomat
* John Wood (Florida politician) (born 1952), member of the Florida House of Representatives
* John Barrett Wood, Canadian politician in the province of Alberta in Alberta general election, 1948

Sport
